AD_COLUMN.NAME: Active
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_COLUMN.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Buttontype
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Classification of button behavior and interaction pattern
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Defines how the button behaves when clicked and what type of user interface it presents. ACTION buttons execute immediate operations, DROPDOWN buttons show a menu of options, MODAL buttons open dialog windows, TOGGLE buttons switch between states, and CUSTOM buttons implement specialized behavior defined in the action handler.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: EM_Etmeta_Color

AD_COLUMN.HELP: Defines a hex code (#RRGGBB) that the new UI will use to display the selected option's color.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Seqno
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Order of appearance within the toolbar section
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Determines the display order of buttons within their assigned toolbar section. Lower numbers appear first (left to right). Buttons with the same sequence number are ordered alphabetically by name. Use increments of 10 to allow for easy insertion of new buttons between existing ones. Each section has an intern section number.
AD_COLUMN.DEFAULTVALUE: @SQL=SELECT COALESCE(MAX(SEQNO),0)+10 AS DefaultValue FROM ETMETA_TOOLBAR_BUTTON WHERE xxParentColumn=@xxParentColumn@

AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Custom JavaScript or server-side logic for button execution
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Contains custom code or configuration that defines specific behavior when the button is clicked. This can include JavaScript functions, server-side process calls, or configuration parameters. Leave empty to use the default behavior defined by the button type and action fields.

AD_COLUMN.NAME: Section
AD_COLUMN.DESCRIPTION: Designated area of the toolbar where the button appears
AD_COLUMN.HELP: Determines the placement of the button within the toolbar layout. LEFT section typically contains primary actions like New and Save, CENTER section holds secondary actions like Delete and Export, and RIGHT section includes utility functions like Searc Filters and Process. This organization helps maintain consistent user interface patterns across the application.
